You can use [regroup][1] template tag, which allow you to group your data when rendering in Django template. Like so:

    {% regroup team_todo_list by author as author_list %}

    {% for author in author_list %}
        &lt;p&gt;Author name: {{ author.grouper }}&lt;/p&gt;
        {% for todo in author.list %}
            &lt;p&gt;Show your todo here {{ todo }}&lt;/p&gt;
        {% endfor %}
    {% endfor %}

- `author` is the keyword which you want to group on
- `author_list` is the list of grouped data
- `.grouper` is the value of the field which you&#39;re grouping on
- `.list` is the list of item which grouped by the field

Hope that helps!

  [1]: https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/2.1/ref/templates/builtins/#regroup

