Well, it&#39;s not all too messy with `awk`. The following replacement of your `while` loop processes the `pstree` output with an `awk` script which determines (on the basis of the position in each line) the tree levels to which the contained processes belong and kills the ones on the selected level `n`.
~~~
while [ $n -gt 1 ]
